      "date": "2013-02-08 17:23:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nAt this point, what to do is unclear.  After pulling at a thread yesterday, I came to the conclusion that it is inadvisable to mix bit fields and masks, so I pulled that code.  What is left is combining the bit fields into the mask word.  This is the result:\n\nlustre/ldlm/ldlm_lock.c:1388: error: 'LDLM_FL_DESTORYED' undeclared\n\nThat value, of course, is #defined in lustre_dlm.h on line 294 as bit 50:\n\n294\t#define LDLM_FL_DESTROYED            0x0004000000000000ULL // bit 50",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
